#decorhacks : shelves can be one of the most difficult decorating challenges. The biggest mistake people make is not properly filling the space. If you can’t be bothered or don’t know what to do, pick large objects that take up nearly the entire height of the shelf, and repeat that same object over and over: try pottery, magazines or baskets. Books turned with the binding facing in and pages facing out also look cohesive, cool and unexpected. Option 2: Give up. Cover your shelves with cabinet doors and pretty hardware. At least you’ll have extra storage.
